From 5c2f1b0b1032b174844e76b161f88e77c1ba98c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Allan Stephens <allan.stephens@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Apr 2012 17:41:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 137/183] tipc: Optimize initialization of network topology
 service
Git-commit: 5c2f1b0b1032b174844e76b161f88e77c1ba98c7
Patch-mainline: Merged into tipc-devel
References: bnc#797455

Initialization now occurs in the calling thread of control,
rather than being deferred to the TIPC tasklet.  With the
current codebase, the deferral is no longer necessary.

Signed-off-by: Allan Stephens <allan.stephens@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: Paul Gortmaker <paul.gortmaker@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: Erik Hugne <erik.hugne@ericsson.com>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Kosina <jkosina@suse.cz>

---
 net/tipc/core.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/tipc/core.c b/net/tipc/core.c
index c8a4f00..ba08940 100644
--- a/net/tipc/core.c
+++ b/net/tipc/core.c
@@ -150,7 +150,7 @@ static int tipc_core_start(void)
 	if (!res)
 		res = tipc_nametbl_init();
 	if (!res)
-		res = tipc_k_signal((Handler)tipc_subscr_start, 0);
+		res = tipc_subscr_start();
 	if (!res)
 		res = tipc_cfg_init();
 	if (!res)
